What a Dockerfile contains:

Instructions: 
These are commands that define 
how the image is built layer by layer.
Each instruction performs a specific action, like copying files,
installing software, or setting environment variables.

Comments: 
Comments explain the purpose of certain instructions or sections of the Dockerfile,
improving readability and maintainability.

Build arguments: 
These are variables that can be passed when building the image, allowing customization 
based on different environments or needs.

Metadata: 
Information like labels, author, and maintainer can be
added to the image for better organization and identification.`